On Wed, 28 Jun 2000, Sarah Nordstrom wrote:
> Just wanted to let anyone who was interested in the POWER port, that
> i've pretty much let it drop, due to a lack of documentation
> available.  Everyone had told me that, but i wanted to see what i
> could do.  The documentation is just plain not available for any
> opensource project at this time, and it doesn't look like IBM's
> planning on making it so, as it's a dead platform really.
> 
> Ohwell, i've got an HP PA-RISC 735/99 i'm going to get Linux on now,
> and mabye make some contributions to that port ;o)
Before dismissing this idea, have a look at
http://www.sjdjweis.com/linux/rs6k/
where this topic has been discussed before. Some work has already been
done. At least the SCSI-drivers and network-adapters are pretty much
the same as the x86 MCA counterparts, and think there are quite some
other hardware that is similar too.
